1
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:48,320
All the surveillance footage from September 8th is here.

2
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,400
Admin!

3
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:54,770
What's going on?

4
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:56,570
I was in the middle of a game.

5
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,720
How can he be so calm?

6
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,080
I can't see his face clearly.

7
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,759
Do you recognize this medicine?

8
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:54,880
Quinocycline.

9
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,960
It's a new type of anti-inflammatory drug.

10
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:58,080
It was just introduced to the country.

11
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,479
It's not widely used yet.

12
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:00,920
Where can I buy this medicine?

13
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,480
A friend of mine distributes this medicine.

14
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,280
Let me ask him.

15
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:06,760
He says

16
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:09,160
it's only sold to three places in total.

17
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,639
One is the City People's Hospital,

18
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:12,000
another is a community clinic,

19
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,460
and the last is a medical aesthetics clinic.

20
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,760
Covered up so tightly.

21
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,600
Plastic surgery.

22
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:48,320
Ask your friend

23
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:51,320
which medical aesthetics clinic uses this medicine.

24
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,800
He says only one plastic surgery hospital uses it.

25
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:04,840
Hello.

26
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,520
You are the friends introduced by Xiao Feng.

27
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,680
Sorry, Dr. Liu,

28
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,680
for calling you over after work.

29
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,320
This is our hospital.

30
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,680
Although our hospital is relatively new,

31
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,600
we have a wealth of experience.

32
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,660
Let's take a look on the second floor.

33
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,290
This is our operating room.

34
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,360
The equipment is imported from Europe and the US.

35
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,600
Our doctors graduated from top universities

36
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:28,460
and have studied in Europe, the US, and South Korea.

37
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:31,400
Whether it's clinical experience or equipment,

38
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,000
we are far ahead of our peers.

39
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,540
These are the medicines we use daily,

40
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:37,240
almost all imported.

41
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,960
And they are the most advanced

42
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:42,560
and cutting-edge products in the medical aesthetics industry.

43
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,800
These are our successful cases.

44
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:47,480
But due to customer privacy issues,

45
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,680
we can't show all of them.

46
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:50,920
Just these.

47
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:52,560
By the way,

48
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,640
who is getting plastic surgery?

49
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,960
You have good facial features,

50
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,560
but there is room for improvement.

51
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,890
For example, your eyes.

52
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,200
They are big, but a bit far apart.

53
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:05,800
Not me.

54
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,480
As for you,

55
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:09,120
there's even more room for improvement.

56
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,000
Not me either.

57
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,800
I understand.

58
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,480
Because of cultural reasons,

59
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:14,800
many people feel a certain level of shame

60
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,320
about plastic surgery.

61
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,980
But it doesn't matter.

62
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,839
Our hospital absolutely guarantees

63
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:21,839
the privacy and security of our clients.

64
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:24,700
Actually, no one is getting plastic surgery today.

65
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:27,480
I also understand the sensitive nature of your industry.

66
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,480
I came today to ask you

67
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,800
to check some client information.

68
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:32,920
Are you kidding me?

69
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:33,840
No.

70
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,370
I have an emergency.

71
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,600
Name your price.

72
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:38,040
I'm a doctor.

73
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,760
We have professional ethics.

74
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,720
We took an oath.

75
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,800
Don't talk about oaths.

76
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,800
I'm really in a hurry right now.

77
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,640
You must have a price.

78
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,440
If you keep this up, I'll call security.

79
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,360
You can call security.

80
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:46,960
Security!

81
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:47,720
What are you doing?

82
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,280
Security!

83
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:48,600
What are you doing?

84
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,000
You...

85
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,280
I just want some information, so what?

86
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:50,880
Security!

87
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:52,400
What are you doing?

88
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:00,560
Dr. Liu,

89
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,920
these are the photos I just took

90
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,080
in your medicine display cabinet.

91
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,560
This medicine is called Sulfalactone.

92
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,440
It is only used

93
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,800
in a small number of European countries.

94
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,680
It hasn't been approved by the domestic FDA.

95
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:15,320
In other words, it's banned domestically.

96
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,610
If I report this to the relevant authorities,

97
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,640
your hospital...

98
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:31,210
Wenjing.

99
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,210
Your food delivery.

100
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:33,800
Yes.

101
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:34,920
Thanks.

102
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:39,720
Dr. Liu.

103
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:42,680
Why are these all paper records?

104
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,930
Are there no electronic versions?

105
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:47,900
Our hospital has its own rules and regulations.

106
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,520
Of course,

107
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,920
it's to better protect client privacy.

108
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,080
All the medical records are here.

109
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,080
Put them back where they belong when you're done.

110
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,320
But I must remind you,

111
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:59,320
these materials were provided by the clients themselves.

112
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:00,920
They might not be authentic.

113
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:01,880
Dr. Liu.

114
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,200
Don't ask any more questions.

115
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,760
I've already made a concession.

116
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,760
If any problems arise in the future,

117
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:08,680
remember,

118
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,400
don't drag me into it.

119
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,120
Have something to eat first.

120
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,400
Here.

121
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,000
Thanks.

122
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,120
I'm sorry

123
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,650
for making you eat takeout.

124
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,159
It's fine.

125
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,000
I never cook at home either.

126
00:06:36,159 --> 00:06:37,220
I only eat takeout.

127
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:38,560
Why?

128
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,820
Don't know how to cook?

129
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,400
I think cooking is pretty boring.

130
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:46,000
Isn't it better to spend time on more important things?

131
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,480
What's wrong?

132
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Does it taste bad?

133
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,880
This tomato and egg dish,

134
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,560
it has vinegar in it.

135
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:06,680
This is my daughter's favorite way of making it.

136
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,200
Really?

137
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,280
I specifically asked the restaurant to make it this way.

138
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:13,440
I thought it was my brother's secret recipe.

139
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,240
No wonder you don't like cooking.

140
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,500
Someone cooks for you.

141
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,120
Yes.

142
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,690
Someone used to make it,

143
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,520
but not anymore.

144
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,200
When I was six,

145
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,960
my parents died in a car crash.

146
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,760
My brother was 16 then.

147
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,440
He was just a kid too.

148
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:40,120
I didn't know what to do at the time.

149
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,280
But my brother,

150
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,720
seemed to grow up overnight.

151
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:48,800
He washed cars, unloaded cargo, and did dishes.

152
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:52,240
He did any job that paid.

153
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,730
He used the money to put me through school.

154
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,400
The two of us just relied on each other to survive.

155
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:03,290
Even though we didn't have parents back then,

156
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,520
he never made me feel unloved.

157
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,840
Sometimes I felt he was a brother

158
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,320
and a father.

159
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,940
Later, I got into medical school,

160
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,520
thinking I would repay him well after graduation.

161
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,680
But another accident happened.

162
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,240
And he was just gone.

163
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,680
You know,

164
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,680
when you just said you were my brother,

165
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,570
I froze for a second.

166
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:38,919
But,

167
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:41,200
you're not as handsome as he was.

168
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,650
You must love your daughter very much.

169
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,260
I'm ashamed to say,

170
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,100
my wife passed away early,

171
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,000
and I raised my kid alone.

172
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,160
Because I used to be a cop,

173
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,490
and quite competitive,

174
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,920
I put a lot of energy into my work

175
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,840
and didn't take good care of her.

176
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,680
But fortunately, my daughter is quite capable.

177
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,460
She is sensible and independent.

178
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,780
She never gave me much to worry about growing up.

179
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,640
You used to be a cop.

180
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,000
Then...

181
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,770
Later, I made a mistake.

182
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,500
Once, I caused a suspect to lose his life,

183
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,580
and was dismissed.

184
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:28,160
Then didn't you have time to spend with your daughter?

185
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:28,880
Yes.

186
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:29,840
But now...

187
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,360
I must make it up to her.

188
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,530
I will never let her get hurt again.

189
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:39,960
Even if

190
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,120
it costs me my life.

191
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,800
With a father like you,

192
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,660
your daughter will be very happy.

193
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:57,600
Li.

194
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,200
That must be her.
